**Method 1:** Recursion. Gets TLE
* Follow binary tree approach in which we take a character from one string and check if it matches
* If yes, then repeat, else backtrack and try other possibilities
* Method 1 will have repeated sub-problems which can be optimized using memoization (method 2)
>**T/S:** O(2 ^ (m + n))/O(m + n), where m = size(s1), n = size(s2)

Example:
![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/030aa1fc-934b-4124-824b-0bad2fe0ecee_1657227944.4161835.png)

```
public boolean isInterleave(String s1, String s2, String s3) {
	var m = s1.length();
	var n = s2.length();
	return m + n == s3.length() && isInterleave(s1, s2, s3, m, n, 0, 0);
}

private boolean isInterleave(String s1, String s2, String s3, int m, int n, int i, int j) {
	return i == m && j == n // reached end of both strings, so interleaving
		|| i < m && s1.charAt(i) == s3.charAt(i + j) && isInterleave(s1, s2, s3, m, n, i + 1, j) // recurse over s1
		|| j < n && s2.charAt(j) == s3.charAt(i + j) && isInterleave(s1, s2, s3, m, n, i, j + 1); // recurse over s2
}
```
**Method 2:** Inject memoization in method 1. Top Down DP (Memoization)
>**T/S:** O(mn)/O(mn)
```
public boolean isInterleave(String s1, String s2, String s3) {
	var m = s1.length();
	var n = s2.length();
	return m + n == s3.length() 
		&& isInterleave(s1, s2, s3, m, n, 0, 0, new Boolean[m + 1][n + 1]);
}

private boolean isInterleave(String s1, String s2, String s3, int m, int n, int i, int j, Boolean[][] memo) {
	if (i == m && j == n)
		return true;
	if (memo[i][j] != null)
		return memo[i][j];

	return memo[i][j] = i < m && s1.charAt(i) == s3.charAt(i + j) && isInterleave(s1, s2, s3, m, n, i + 1, j, memo) 
					 || j < n && s2.charAt(j) == s3.charAt(i + j) && isInterleave(s1, s2, s3, m, n, i, j + 1, memo);
}
```
**Method 3:** Top Down Tabulation version of method 2
* Same idea, just iterative
>**T/S:** O(mn)/O(mn)
```
public boolean isInterleave(String s1, String s2, String s3) {
	var m = s1.length();
	var n = s2.length();
	if (m + n != s3.length())
		return false;

	var dp = new boolean[m + 1][n + 1];
	dp[m][n] = true;

	for (var i = m; i >= 0; i--)
		for (var j = n; j >= 0; j--)
			if (i < m && s1.charAt(i) == s3.charAt(i + j) && dp[i + 1][j] 
			 || j < n && s2.charAt(j) == s3.charAt(i + j) && dp[i][j + 1])				
				dp[i][j] = true;

	return dp[0][0];
}
```
**Method 4:** Bottom Up DP (Tabulation)
* For each cell consider only the strings upto that point
* For the top left corner, both strings are empty and interleave to empty portion of s2, so `isInterleave = true`
* For the first column s2 is considered empty and for first row s1 is considered empty. Now fill out if the corresponding letter of s1 and s3 match. Repeat for s2 and s3. E.g.
	* s1 = aabcc, s3 = aadbbcbcac, matches occur for first 2 letters so the value is true, rest are false
* For cell (2, 2), consider the strings s1 = aa, s2 = db, s3 = aadb
	* Check top neighbor (remove 1 char from s1), i.e. s1 = a, s2 = db. Its false, so do nothing. False is expected since a and db can't be interleaved in any way to form the first 3 letters of s3 
	* Check left neighbot (remove 1 char from s2), i.e. s1 = aa, s2 = d. Its true, so check next condition. True is expected because `aa` and `d`  can be interleaved to form the first 3 letters of s3.
		* Next condition is to check whether current char of s2 is the same as current char of s3, which is true since they both are b
		* Since both the conditions are true, it means s1 and s2 can be interleaved to form s3, thus the value here would be true
* Continue doing this for complete strings s1 and s2. Value in bottom right corner will be the answer since that denotes the end of the interleaving of 2 strings

Example: `s1 = aabcc, s2 = dbbca, s3 = aadbbcbcac`

![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/ef2f6ce0-615f-4a6b-93e2-ce34fcfff488_1657228807.3073637.png)

>**T/S:** O(mn)/O(mn)
```
public boolean isInterleave(String s1, String s2, String s3) {
	var m = s1.length();
	var n = s2.length();
	if (m + n != s3.length())
		return false;

	var dp = new boolean[m + 1][n + 1];
	dp[0][0] = true;

	for (var i = 0; i < m && dp[i][0]; i++)
		dp[i + 1][0] = s1.charAt(i) == s3.charAt(i) && dp[i][0];

	for (var j = 0; j < n && dp[0][j]; j++)
		dp[0][j + 1] = s2.charAt(j) == s3.charAt(j) && dp[0][j];

	for (var i = 1; i <= m; i++)
		for (var j = 1; j <= n; j++)
			dp[i][j] = dp[i - 1][j] && s1.charAt(i - 1) == s3.charAt(i + j - 1)
					|| dp[i][j - 1] && s2.charAt(j - 1) == s3.charAt(i + j - 1);

	return dp[m][n];
}
```
**Method 5:** Space optimized version of Method 3
* In any iteration only the current row and previous row of dp is being used, so we need only 2 rows, not m
>**T/S:** O(mn)/O(n)
```
public boolean isInterleave(String s1, String s2, String s3) {
	var m = s1.length();
	var n = s2.length();
	if (m + n != s3.length())
		return false;

	var dp = new boolean[n + 1];

	for (var i = 0; i <= m; i++)
		for (var j = 0; j <= n; j++) {
			var first = j != 0 && dp[j - 1] && s2.charAt(j - 1) == s3.charAt(i + j - 1);
			var second = i != 0 && dp[j] && s1.charAt(i - 1) == s3.charAt(i + j - 1);

			if (i == 0 && j == 0)
				dp[j] = true;
			else if (i == 0)
				dp[j] = first;
			else if (j == 0)
				dp[j] = second;
			else
				dp[j] = first || second;
		}
	return dp[n];
}
```

