# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
**if we can represent each node of the tree uniquely**, then we can easily serialize the tree into a string and deserialize the string back to the original binary tree. This is because the inorder and preorder traversals of a binary tree (with unique node values) uniquely define the tree.

**How do we represent each node uniquely as a string?**
To represent each node uniquely, we can concatenate the address of the node to its value (as ***"val_address"***). **This ensures that even if there are duplicate values in the tree, we can able to represent each node uniquely as the address is unique for each node**.
```
    1
   / \
  2   3
 / \
4   5
```
Representation example for this given tree:-
```
Preorder string : "1_0x1000 2_0x1004 4_0x1008 5_0x100c 3_0x1010"
Inorder string :  "4_0x1008 2_0x1004 5_0x100c 1_0x1000 3_0x1010"
Overall tree can be represented as :-
"4_0x1008 2_0x1004 5_0x100c 1_0x1000 3_0x1010 $ 1_0x1000 2_0x1004 4_0x1008 5_0x100c 3_0x1010 "
```

# Approach
**serialize(TreeNode * root)**: This method serializes the binary tree root into a string. The string will be in the format of 
```
"inorder_traversal_string $ preorder_traversal_string"
```

**deserialize(string data)**: This method deserializes the binary tree from the string data. The string must be in the format of 
```
"inorder_traversal_string $ preorder_traversal_string"
```
## Helper functions definition : -
**getAddressAsString(const TreeNode * node)**: This method gets the address of the node as a string.

**extractVal(string &s)**: This method extracts the value of a node from the string s. The string must be in the format of 
```
"val_address"
```
> **We have store every node as *"val_address"* to represent every node uniquely so that we can generate unique tree from given preorder and inorder traversal even if there are multiples nodes with same values in the tree.**

**inorder(TreeNode *root, string &serialstr)**: This method traverses the binary tree root in inorder and stores the values *(as "value_address")* of the nodes in the string serialstr.

**preorder(TreeNode *root, string &serialstr)**: This method traverses the binary tree root in preorder and stores the values *(as "value_address")* of the nodes in the string serialstr.

**genTree(int in_s, int in_e, int pre_s, int pre_e, vector< string> &inorder, vector< string> &preorder)**: This method constructs a binary tree from the inorder and preorder traversals inorder and preorder.

---

**To serialize the binary tree, the following steps are performed:**

- The inorder traversal of the tree is performed and the values of the nodes are stored in a string serialstr.
- The preorder traversal of the tree is performed and the values of the nodes are stored in a string serialstr.
- The two strings are concatenated and returned.

**To deserialize the binary tree, the following steps are performed:**

- The string data is split into two strings: the inorder traversal and the preorder traversal.
- The inorder traversal( *as vector< string> where each node is represented as "val_address"*) is used to find the index of the root node given by the 0th index in the preorder traversal.
- Then we recursively construct the left and right subtrees of the root node.
- The root node is returned.

# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(n)
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: O(n)
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
/**
 * Definition for a binary tree node.
 * struct TreeNode {
 *     int val;
 *     TreeNode *left;
 *     TreeNode *right;
 *     TreeNode(int x) : val(x), left(NULL), right(NULL) {}
 * };
 */
class Codec {
public:
    int extractVal(string &s)
    {
        stringstream ss(s);
        string str;
        while(getline(ss,str,'_'))
        {
            return stoi(str);
        }
        return 0; //it is not executed
    }
    string getAddressAsString(const TreeNode* node) {
        ostringstream oss;
        oss << static_cast<const void*>(node);
        return oss.str();
    }
    void inorder(TreeNode *root,string &serialstr)
    {
        if(root==NULL) return;
        inorder(root->left,serialstr);
        serialstr+=((to_string(root->val)+"_"+getAddressAsString(root))+" ");
        inorder(root->right,serialstr);
    }
    void preorder(TreeNode *root,string &serialstr)
    {
        if(root==NULL) return;
        serialstr+=((to_string(root->val)+"_"+getAddressAsString(root))+" ");
        preorder(root->left,serialstr);
        preorder(root->right,serialstr);
    }
    //  function to contruct tree from inorder and preorder array
    TreeNode* genTree(int in_s,int in_e,int pre_s,int pre_e,vector<string> &inorder,vector<string> &preorder)
    {
        /*
        in_s,in_e-> start index, end index (both included) of inorder array.
        pre_s,pre_e-> start index, end index (both included) of preorder array.
        */
        if(in_s>in_e) return NULL;
        //extract the root value from the string
        TreeNode *root=new TreeNode(extractVal(preorder[pre_s]));
        int idx;
        for(int i=in_s;i<=in_e;i++)
        {
            if(inorder[i]==preorder[pre_s])
            {
                idx=i;break;
            }
        }
        int leftsize=idx-in_s;
        int rightsize=in_e-idx;
        //construct left subtree
        root->left=genTree(in_s,idx-1,pre_s+1,pre_s+leftsize,inorder,preorder);
        root->right=genTree(idx+1,in_e,pre_s+leftsize+1,pre_e,inorder,preorder);
        return root;
    }
    // Encodes a tree to a single string.
    string serialize(TreeNode* root) {
        // we will store inorder and preoder in string seperated by " $ "
        string serialstr;
        inorder(root,serialstr);
        serialstr+="$ ";
        preorder(root,serialstr);
        return serialstr;
    }

    // Decodes your encoded data to tree.
    TreeNode* deserialize(string data) {
        stringstream ss(data); // using stringstream to tokenize the string wrt delimeter
        //then we use getline to access each string in stringstream into another string 
        string str;
        bool seperator_seen=0;
        vector<string> inorder,preorder;
        while(getline(ss,str,' '))
        {
            if(str=="$")
            {
                seperator_seen=1;
            }
            else{
                if(seperator_seen==0)
                {
                    inorder.push_back(str);
                }
                else preorder.push_back(str);
            }
        }
        //now contruct the binary tree from inorder and preorder
        return genTree(0,inorder.size()-1,0,preorder.size()-1,inorder,preorder);
    }
};

// Your Codec object will be instantiated and called as such:
// Codec ser, deser;
// TreeNode* ans = deser.deserialize(ser.serialize(root));
```
