solutions.content:
**Tree format**: `<Tree> := (), or <Tree> := (<Value><Tree><Tree>)`

**Serialization**: Build string representation using `StringBuilder` (concatenating `String`s is expensive) and **pre-order traversal**.

**Deserialization**:
Instead of iterating over the serialized input to find the matching closing bracket, I handle this in `O(n)` during the "pre-processing" stage:
I build an array mapping the index of any **opening** bracket to its corresponding **closing** bracket, using a `Stack`.

Because the format is known, the recursive method only needs to look up the closing index for its left subtree, using this array.

```
public class Codec {

    // Encodes a tree to a single string.
    public String serialize(TreeNode root) {
        StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder(); // appending char to a StringBuilder is O(1)
        this.serializeHelper(sb, root);
        return sb.toString();
    }

    private void serializeHelper(StringBuilder sb, TreeNode root) {
        sb.append('(');
        if(root != null) { // recursive pre-order traversal
            sb.append(root.val);
            this.serializeHelper(sb, root.left);
            this.serializeHelper(sb, root.right);
        }
        sb.append(')');
    }

    // Decodes your encoded data to tree.
    public TreeNode deserialize(String data) {
        char[] tree = data.toCharArray();
        int[] matchingBraces = new int[tree.length]; // O(1) lookup of matching closing bracket (eliminates the need to iterate over "tree")
        Stack<Integer> openingIdxs = new Stack<>(); // pop/push to match corresponding brackets
        for(int i = 0; i < tree.length; i++) {
            if(tree[i] == '(') {
                openingIdxs.push(i);
            } else if(tree[i] == ')') {
                matchingBraces[openingIdxs.pop()] = i;
            }
        }
        return this.deserializeHelper(tree, matchingBraces, 0, tree.length - 1);
    }

    private TreeNode deserializeHelper(char[] tree, int[] closingBraces, int lo, int hi) {
        if(hi - lo == 1) {
            return null;
        }
        int value = 0;
        boolean negativeValue = false;
        if(tree[lo + 1] == '-') {
            negativeValue = true;
            lo++;
        }
        while(tree[++lo] != '(') {
            value *= 10;
            value += tree[lo] - '0';
        }
        if(negativeValue) {
            value *= -1;
        }
        TreeNode root = new TreeNode(value);
        int leftEnd = closingBraces[lo]; // O(1) lookup
        root.left = this.deserializeHelper(tree, closingBraces, lo, leftEnd);
        root.right = this.deserializeHelper(tree, closingBraces, leftEnd + 1, hi - 1);
        return root;
    }
}
```

