<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Everything is given in description. Just keep in mind that if you are optimising your recursion function then it might give you runtime error (if you are considering vector & blindly converting recursive code to memoization or dp. Because, when n is odd, you need dp of size (n+2)). So, for safety purpose, I have used map.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
