solutions.content:
**Lets take an example**
n = 47

Lets take two path
n = 47-> 48 ->24->12->6->3->2->1 (**7 Steps** in Total)
and
n = 47 ->46->23->22->11->10->5->4->2->1 (**9 Steps** in total)

so we need to choose carefully and look at detail

47 -> 101111
48 -> 110000
46 -> 101110

now right shift (divide by 2) multiple times we will observe that occurance of 1 at LSB (Odd) is more in 46 is more than 48. So, it is better to choose 48. So we will count no of zeros (unset bits) in right side of bit representation in both the cases of n-1 and n+1. The one with most zeros will be chosen.


***CODE***
```
int integerReplacement(int n) {

        if(n==INT_MAX) return 32;
        int count  = 0;
        while(n>3){
            if(n%2==0){
                // if n is even
                n=n>>1;
            }else{
                // if n is odd
                int increment = n+1;
                int decrement = n-1;
                int unsetBits = 0;

                while(!(increment&1)){
                    unsetBits++;
                    increment = increment>>1;
                }
                while(!(decrement&1)){
                    unsetBits--;
                    decrement = decrement>>1;
                }
                if(unsetBits>0){
                    n = n+1;
                }else{
                    n = n-1;
                }
            }
            count++;
        }

        if(n<=3) count+=(n-1);

        return count;
    }
```

