solutions.content:
If the number is even we simply divide by 2 and continue, but if the number is odd, we can either go forward or backwards, and to decide that, we can greedily check which one of the two has greater last set bit. We can find the last set bit using the formula n&(-n). The exception is for 3, in which we go backwards.
```
class Solution:
    def integerReplacement(self, n: int) -> int:
        cnt = 0
        while n>1:
            if n&1:
                if (n-1)&(1-n) >= (n+1)&(-1-n) or n == 3:
                    n -= 1
                else:
                    n += 1
            else:
                n >>= 1
            cnt += 1
        return cnt
```

