if n is odd...we first check  if we increment it by 1 is its half divisible by 2...this is bcoz if its divisible by 2 we get to divide it in the next step which reduces the size of n to n/2 which is alot of reduction...on the contrary if its half isnt divisble by 2 it will lead to extra operations

