Proof:
F(n) is the return value of the function. Prove by induction that

- |F(k)-F(k+1)| <= 1

When parameter is less than 2N, suppose the result is true, then

- F(2N) = 1 + F(N)
- F(2N+1) = 1 + min(F(N), F(N+1))
- F(2N+2) = 1 + F(N+1)

Easy to check the result is true. So we can find,

- F(4k+1) = min(2 + F(2k), 2 + F(2k+1)) = min(3 + F(k), 4 + F(k+1)) = 3 + F(k)
- F(4k+3) = 3 + F(k+1)

or equivalently, F(2n+1) = 3 + F( floor( (n+1)/4 ) )

