solutions.content:
after finding the node, put the left child (if any) of its right child to the deepest right child of its left child, then the new left child of current right child will be current left child. return right child as new root 
```
class Solution:
    def helper(self, root, key):
      if not root:
        return None
      else:
        if root.val == key:
          if not root.left and not root.right:
            return None
          elif root.left and not root.right:
            return root.left
          elif root.right and not root.left:
            return root.right
          else:
            left_right_most = root.left
            prev = left_right_most
            while left_right_most:
              prev = left_right_most
              left_right_most = left_right_most.right
            prev.right = root.right.left
            root.right.left = root.left
            return root.right
        elif root.val > key:
          root.left = self.helper(root.left, key)
        elif root.val < key:
          root.right = self.helper(root.right, key)
        return root

    def deleteNode(self, root: TreeNode, key: int) -> TreeNode:
      return self.helper(root, key)
```

